6.2.3 Disable Animations
All platforms, apps, and websites must allow users to deactivate animations, blinking, or moving content, reducing distractions and helping users with sensory sensitivities or cognitive disabilities.

6.2.3-A
Users must have the option to disable animations, moving, blinking, or scrolling content, which can cause distractions or seizures for some users, as discussed in section 2.1.1. This aligns with WCAG 2.1 2.3.1 and WCAG 2.1 2.2.2.
